# project-workflow

Spec-driven development with GitHub Copilot.

A lightweight, opinionated workflow framework for using AI agents to scaffold, clarify, plan, and implement features with built-in task tracking, requirements validation, and iterative prompts.

## Quick Start

Bootstrap the workflow in your project:

```bash
uvx --from git+https://github.com/johndetlefs/project-workflow.git project init
```

This command:
- ✅ Creates `.project-workflow/` directory structure
- ✅ Creates `.github/prompts/` with AI agent prompts (Clarify, Implement, Planner, Requirements, Scaffold)
- ✅ Sets up `.project-workflow/TRACKER.md` for task management
- ✅ Copies the local workflow CLI to `.project-workflow/cli/`
- ✅ Idempotent—safe to run multiple times; detects conflicts and asks before overwriting

## Workflow

After bootstrapping, you have two layers:

### 1. Bootstrap layer (uvx)

```bash
# First-time setup in a new project
uvx --from git+https://github.com/johndetlefs/project-workflow.git project init
```

### 2. Local workflow layer (.project-workflow/cli)

Once initialized, use the local workflow CLI to scaffold and manage tasks:

```bash
# Create a new task
./.project-workflow/cli/workflow task init \
  --id APP-001 \
  --title "My Feature" \
  --update-tracker

# With optional git branch
./.project-workflow/cli/workflow task init \
  --id APP-001 \
  --title "My Feature" \
  --update-tracker \
  --create-branch
```

## Prompts (in .github/prompts/)

After running `project init`, use these AI agent prompts with GitHub Copilot:

- **Requirements.prompt.md** — Discover and document what you're building
- **Clarify.prompt.md** — Resolve ambiguities before planning
- **Planner.prompt.md** — Turn requirements into a phased implementation plan
- **Implement.prompt.md** — Execute changes with validation and tracker updates
- **Scaffold.prompt.md** — Create task scaffolding (wrapper around the CLI)

## Project Structure

Once initialized:

```
your-repo/
├── .project-workflow/
│   ├── TRACKER.md               # Task status tracker
│   ├── cli/
│   │   ├── workflow             # Shell wrapper
│   │   └── workflow.py          # Local CLI (task scaffolding)
│   └── tasks/
│       └── APP-001-My-Feature/
│           ├── IMPLEMENTATION.md  # User story + task list
│           └── REQUIREMENTS.md    # Goals, acceptance criteria, decisions
└── .github/
    └── prompts/                 # AI agent prompts (editable)
        ├── Clarify.prompt.md
        ├── Implement.prompt.md
        ├── Planner.prompt.md
        ├── Requirements.prompt.md
        └── Scaffold.prompt.md
```

## Documentation

- [Local workflow CLI README](.project-workflow/cli/README.md) — Task scaffolding and branch creation
- [AI Prompt Guide](.github/prompts/) — How to use the spec-driven workflow with GitHub Copilot

## Design Philosophy

- **Spec-first**: Write requirements before code
- **Iterative**: Clarify ambiguities before planning; refine requirements with AI
- **Traceable**: All changes tied to task IDs in TRACKER.md
- **Automation-friendly**: Structured markdown for AI agents to read and update
- **No vendor lock-in**: Plain Markdown files, stdlib Python, git-native workflows

